## Component Classes

Use the following structural classes when building prototypes or production UI. When AI generates markup, normalize it to these classes during refinement.

### Buttons

```html
<!-- Variants -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
<button class="btn btn-teal">Teal</button>
<button class="btn btn-orange">Orange</button>
<button class="btn btn-danger">Danger</button>
<button class="btn btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
<button class="btn btn-action">Actions ▾</button>

<!-- Sizes -->
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Small</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary">Default</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Large</button>
```

**Button behavior guidelines**

- Primary actions use `btn-primary` with `--follett-blue-medium` and live in consistent locations (bottom-right of forms, top-right of pages).  
- Destructive actions always use `btn-danger` and pair with confirmation patterns.  
- Ghost / secondary actions are visually de-emphasized and never compete with the primary CTA.

