### Cards & Layout

```html
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">…</div>
</div>

<div class="stats-grid">
  <!-- Static stat card -->
  <div class="stat-card">
    <div class="stat-icon blue">…</div> <!-- blue | orange | red | green -->
    <div class="stat-content">
      <h4>142</h4>
      <p>AI Tools Registered</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Clickable/navigable stat card — adds hover style + arrow affordance -->
  <div class="stat-card stat-card-link" onClick={…}>
    <div class="stat-icon red">…</div>
    <div class="stat-content">
      <h4>8</h4>
      <p>Vendor Risk Alerts</p>
    </div>
    <ChevronRight size={16} className="stat-link-arrow" />
  </div>
</div>
```

> **`.stat-card-link` behavior:** On hover, the card background shifts to `--follett-blue-lighter`, border turns `--follett-blue-medium`, subtitle text picks up the blue, and the arrow nudges 3px right.  
> Use this class any time a stat card navigates somewhere, and always pair with a `ChevronRight` icon carrying the `.stat-link-arrow` class.

---

### Tables

```html
<div class="table-container">
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Column</th>
        <!-- more columns -->
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="clickable">
        <td>…</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

Guidelines:

- Column headers use `Label` typography (12px, uppercase) with clear sort affordances where applicable.  
- Clickable rows use `.clickable` plus hover background (`--follett-blue-lighter`) and cursor pointer.  
- Never rely on color alone to indicate row state; pair with icons or badges.

---

### Forms

```html
<div class="form-row">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label class="form-label">Field Name</label>
    <input class="form-input" type="text" placeholder="…" />
  </div>
</div>

<div class="form-group">
  <label class="form-label">Select Field</label>
  <select class="form-select">
    …
  </select>
</div>

<div class="form-group">
  <label class="form-label">Description</label>
  <textarea class="form-textarea"></textarea>
</div>

<label class="form-checkbox">
  <input type="checkbox" />
  Label text
</label>
```

Form behavior:

- Group related fields into logical sections with H3/H4 headings.  
- Always show required vs optional explicitly (e.g., “School Name *” or inline “Required”).  
- Validation messages appear directly under the field using `Small` text and appropriate status color.

---

### Tabs

```html
<div class="tabs">
  <button class="tab active">Tab One</button>
  <button class="tab">Tab Two</button>
</div>
```

- Use tabs to separate closely related content (e.g., Summary / Details / History), not unrelated features.  
- The active tab must always be visually obvious (`--follett-blue-medium`, bold text, underline or bottom border).

